{
  "stem": "1799.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 610.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it became almost animal-like by then.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I witnessed human beings behaving substandard and uncivilized.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And all they were thinking of was food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Stealing, stealing, beating.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were certain hierarchies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were certain people who were stronger than other people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if it wasn't known to the camp guards, they would take advantage of that too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I-- by then I had no more fellow inmates that I knew from this transport from France.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- we had separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the one other surviving young gentlemen, Wolfgang [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Blumenreich, ?] had now left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was to see him again later in Birkenau, but I had not seen him for-- by that time, we were apart for over a year.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I ran into him again in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a large camp, and I don't remember its name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was-- I never, in my life, thought that human beings could survive in substandards such as the, the conditions in that camp offered, or did not offer.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And yet people were not yet dying at the rate I saw them die later on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were still holding on.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
